How can you serve cold cheese on a breakfast sandwich? They also have a sign before you go in saying something about how important it is to treat people well or make them feel welcome or something along those lines, but my experience was anything but that. There was no one at the register when I walked in, and though there were several people working, no one acknowledged me for at least a minute. That's a long time in customer service minutes. I wasn't sure where to place my order, and the cashier was not very friendly when he finally decided to take my order. Better than Dunkin (they have an actually-boiled shine!), but nowhere near as good as an actual NYC bagel.

As close to being a real NYC deli as I've seen anywhere outside of NYC! Great bagels with a variety of cream cheeses, boars head meats and tuna/egg/chicken salads.

Good place to get bagels in the city, best have a person in the car with you so you can run in and grab your food if you don't want to park. Awesome sandys and good cream cheese make this place a good spot to grab a quick bite.

Attention if you are from Jersey!!! They have Taylor Ham, Great Bagels, and high quality deli meats... If you are homesick and looking for a taste from home stop here!!! Only downside is lack of tastykakes.
NYC Bagel Deli has THE BEST low fat tuna salad, and you can purchase by the pound.   I go a few times a week for lunch and love my bagel fix!  Highly recommend.

Bagelicious and now located close to my house (North Ave) and Close to my office (Dearborn).  Even though i get breakfast provided for free at work, I still stop by at least once a week for a breakfast sandwich from NYCBD. Very excited that they now serve Intelligentsia Coffee.Love the high quality products, speed factor and super friendly staff!  Can't wait to try their new menu option - NY style pizza!

I love love love NYC bagel hands down the best bagel in the city of Chicago.  Corey's crew is incredibly hard working and some of the friendliest people you'll ever meet. The newer location has a more unique setup then the original at North & Sheffield but the bagels are delicious and the Intelligentsia coffee is divine.  You might spend a few more dollars here then other chain bagel places that shall remain nameless but the difference in quality makes it worth every cent.  Whether it's breakfast or lunch you can't go wrong with NYC Bagel.
